annotationA: Rigor mortis is a component of the cytoplasmic U snRNP body and a member of the SMN-Gemins complex. It is required in the motor system for viability and motor behaviour. It also works as a nuclear receptor interacting protein required for ecdysone signalling during larval development
annotationB: FI05704p; Protein binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: regulation of alternative mRNA splicing, via spliceosome; histone mRNA 3'-end processing
